<p>The design requirements for the <a
href="../capabilities/blackbodies.html">HIRDLS
In-flight Calibration Blackbody, IFCBB</a> specified 10&#160;mK absolute
accuracy at the point of calibration, with shifts of no more than 5&#160;mK
per year and with traceability back to ITS90. This exacting
specification was met through the application of rigorous sensor
procurement, conditioning and selection procedures prior to blackbody
integration. The assembled blackbody was then 'thermally conditioned'
and thermometrically calibrated as a single unit (including the flight
harness) in the cryostat shown in Fig 1.  <TABLE WIDTH=100%
