<p>The cryostat, which has an operational temperature range from 200 K
to 345 K (cooled with a Huber refrigeration unit), has been used on a
number of occasions to calibrate temperatures sensors or small
blackbodies, or a combination of both. The thermometer block used to
calibrate the blackbody targets and sea water temperature probes for
the <a
href="http://www.atsr.rl.ac.uk/validation/sister/sis_inst/index.shtml">SISTeR
calibration campaign</a> is shown in Fig 2, with the assembled block,
prior to installing in the cryostat, shown in Fig 3. The block was
fitted with a Tinsley gas-filled PRT (P/N 5187L) calibrated at NPL to
ITS90. A similar arrangement, involving a purpose-built thermometer
block, was used to calibrate the HIRDLS in-flight calibrator
blackbody.</p> <TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLPADDING="5%"><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>
<CENTER>
